Sentencas: cathode supporter, LSM-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (SDC) cathode functional layer (CFL), yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ)/SDC bi-layered electrolyte and Ni-YSZ anode layer was fabricated by a slurry spin coating technique.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical properties of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: The influence of the porosity in both the CFL and cathode supporter on the electrochemical properties of the cells has been investigated.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical properties of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: It was found that properly controlling the porosity in the CFL would improve the performance of the cells using 02 in the cathode side (O-2-cells), with a maximum power density (MPD) value achieving as high as 0.58 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical properties of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: However, this improvement is not so evident for the cells using air in the cathode side (air-cells).
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical properties of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: When increasing the porosity in the cathode-supporter, a significant increase of the power density for the air cells due to the decreasing R-conc,R-c (cathode concentration polarization to the cell resistance) can be ascertained.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical properties of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: In terms of our analysis on various electrochemical parameters, the R-act (activation polarization to the cell resistance) is assumed to be mainly responsible for the impedance arcs measured under the OCV condition, with a negligible R-conc,R-c value being able to be detected in our impedances.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical properties of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: In this case, a significant decreasing size of the impedance arcs due to the increasing porosity in the cathode supporter would correspond to a decrease of the R-act values, which was proved to be induced by the decreasing R-conc,R-c. (C) 2012 Elsevier Ltd.
